# `Cargo.lock` is deliberately NOT ignored (#129). This crate is a detached
# workspace, so the root lockfile does not cover it, and `cargo fuzz` accepts no
# `--locked` flag — leaving its dependency set free to drift silently on every
# run. Tracking the lockfile lets CI assert it instead, with
# `cargo metadata --locked` ahead of the fuzz build.
#
# Cost of this: changing a dependency of `notepad-core` or `notepad-syntax` also
# makes *this* lockfile stale, and CI will say so. Regenerate it with:
#   cargo generate-lockfile --manifest-path crates/core/fuzz/Cargo.toml
